=== Noun phrase ===
'''lame duck''' (''plural'' '''lame ducks''')
# ''(U.S. colloquial)'' political terminology: an elected official who has lost the recent election or is not [[eligible]] for [[reelection]] and is [[marking time]] until leaving office
#* Congressman Jones was a '''lame duck''' and did not vote on many issues that were important to his [[constituent]]s.
# ''(colloquial)'' a person or thing that is helpless, [[inefficient]] or [[disabled]]
